google_play_reviews.content: confused.. about the whole free api key stuff . I managed to get an API key, it checks out, but says I still require a 'onecall' subscription.. which wants me to pay. So if there is some free personal use plan, I am not figuring it out.
google_play_reviews.replyContent: QuickWeather requires the "OneCall" subscription from OpenWeatherMap. You get 1000 free API calls daily with "OneCall". You are required to provide billing information to OpenWeatherMap, but you are only billed if you go over the free daily limit. You can set a limit in OpenWeatherMap settings so that you do not exceed the free daily API calls

google_play_reviews.content: I really like this app so far. It would be great if the ongoing notification had options for showing the current temperature.
google_play_reviews.replyContent: Thank you for the feedback. The ongoing notification already displays the current temperature for your currently selected location. If you are encountering any issues or would like to give additional feedback, you can do so on the Issue Tracker - https://github.com/TylerWilliamson/QuickWeather/issues
